title: No 'out' folder created on "forge build"
body:
### Component

Forge

### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?

- [X] Foundry
- [X] Foundryup

### What version of Foundry are you on?

forge 0.2.0 (59f9604 2022-05-30T12:42:45.5196153Z)

### What command(s) is the bug in?

forge build

### Operating System

Windows

### Describe the bug

Foundry does not generate the `out` folder upon building. 
This has been first observed after upgrading Foundry to commit `b192af4`. Previous version was also Foundry 0.2.0, although I cannot remember the specific commit.
As a result of this, no tests are detected. No scripts can be ran either.

Steps taken:

- `forge clean`
- `forge build`
- `forge test`

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/104004836/170998527-4c55aea5-9c89-45fa-a978-428e2760fb47.png)

- re-installing foundry from source

Neither solved the issue.

The `cache` folder is generated, along with a `solidity-files-cache.json` (which seems to hold quite some content, it's not an empty file).
